events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Anthony Davis had 34 points and 15 rebounds to help the Los Angeles Lakers beat the San Antonio Spurs 114-106 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Davis has 34 points and 15 rebounds, Lakers beat Spurs

headlines.description: — Trae Young and the Atlanta Hawks have struggled under the weight of increased expectations.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young scores 42 points, Hawks beat Bucks to snap 6-game skid

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Charlotte Hornets

headlines.description: — Terry Rozier sought out Charlotte Hornets teammate Mason Plumlee, the team's 7-foot center, after the game Sunday night game and joked with him that he plans to handle all jump balls going forward.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bridges, Rozier help Hornets snap Warriors 7-game win streak

headlines.description: — Devin Booker had 26 points and six assists and the Phoenix Suns won their eighth straight game and handed Houston its 11th loss in a row, routing the Rockets 115-89 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Suns win 8th straight, hand Rockets 11th loss in a row

events.name: Brooklyn Nets at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant made himself at home again in Oklahoma City.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kevin Durant scores 33 points, Nets beat Thunder 120-96

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic just missed out on his third straight triple-double, finishing with 28 points, nine rebounds and nine assists, and the Denver Nuggets spoiled Chauncey Billups' return with a 124-95 victory over the Portland Trail Blazers on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic has 28 points, Nuggets rout Trail Blazers, 124-95

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan scored 35 points and Zach LaVine added 29 to help the Chicago Bulls beat the Los Angeles Clippers 100-90 on Sunday night, ending the Clippers’ seven-game winning streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeRozan, LaVine in double digits, Bulls end Clippers' streak
